  ✓ algorithmic
      Speedup: 1.72x
      - Implemented a different dataflow than the current one: instead of computing all four pooled convolution pixels independently, the Triton kernel computes the two horizontally adjacent convolution outputs together for each vertical pool row. This preserves the required `conv -> ReLU -> avgpool` order but reuses the shared 3x4 input patch, reducing input vector loads from 36 to 24 per pooled output while keeping the same DPAS dot count. Weight packing and zero-bias caching from the prior optimized 
